===Etymology===
From {{term|占める|tr=shimeru|lang=ja}}, as cursive form of top component ト (also [[〆]]). Then applied to other kanji of the same pronunciation, namely 締め, 閉め, and 絞め, all pronounced しめ ''shime.'' Sense of “closed, fastened” is due to {{term|閉める||to close|tr=shimeru|lang=ja}} and {{term|締める||to fasten|tr=shimeru|lang=ja}}.

